accessrestrict.head: Access to Collection
accessrestrict.p: The materials are open for research use. Audio-visual materials are not available in original format, and must be reformatted to a digital use copy.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Duncan McNaughton is an American poet, scholar, cultural critic, small press editor, and a founder/publisher of several seminal magazines. McNaughton also established the Poetics Program at the New College of California in San Francisco and directed the program from its opening in 1965 until 1990. The Collection contains manuscripts, notebooks, correspondence, and material concerning the New College.
